@@TJvDropTarget
<TITLEIMG TJvDropTarget>
#JVCLInfo
<GROUP JVCL.System, JVCL.FormsAndApp.Forms>
<FLAG Component>
Summary
  Enables a control to accepts dropped files.
Description
  Use TJvDropTarget to enable a control to accept dropped files.
  
  To use a TJvDropTarget, do the following:
  
  * Drop a TJvDropTarget component on a form.
  * Set Control to the control that should accept dropped files.
  * Set property AcceptDrag to true; this means that now the control accepts dropped files.
  * Write an OnDragDrop event handler, that will respond when the user drops files on the <LINK
  TJvDropTarget.Control, drop target>. Use the methods of the component in the event handle, to
  retrieve the file names, content etc. of the dropped files.

